                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="planning">
                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> 10 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 25 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 10-12 muffins <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Muffin tin</li>
                    <li>Food processor</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Group 1</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Whole grain spelt flour, 2 1/4 cups (285g)</li>
                        <li>Coconut sugar, 1/4 cups</li>
                        <li>Cinnamon, 1 tsp</li>
                        <li>Allspice, 1/2 tsp</li>
                        <li>Sea salt, 1/4 tsp</li>
                        <li>Ground ginger, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Baking powder, 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking soda, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Blackstrap molasses, 2 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>Unsweetened applesauce, 1/2 cup</li>
                    <li>Plain non-dairy milk, 3/4 cups</li>
                    <li>Maple syrup, 1/3 cup</li>
                    <li>Vanilla extract, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Blueberries, 2/3 - 3/4 cup</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 350Â°</li>
                    <li>Line muffin tin</li>
                    <li>In a large bowl, combine the Group 1 ingredients</li>
                    <li>Sift in the baking power and baking soda</li>
                    <li>Stir until all is well combined</li>
                    <li>In a medium bowl, combine molasses and applesauce</li>
                    <li>Whick in the milk, maple syrup, and vanilla extract, mixing together</li>
                    <li>Fold the wet into the dry and mix until just combined</li>
                    <li>Fold in the berries</li>
                    <li>Spoon into muffin tin</li>
                    <li>Bake 22-24 minutes</li>
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Yum</li>
                    <li>Coconut sugar can be replaced with other unrefined sugar</li>

                </ul>

            </div>

